data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your manual `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` construction won't compile. Replace with a simple lambda:

```csharp
// .NET 10 — no expression trees needed
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes

**a) Duplicate property names are now uniquified.** Your `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` will get auto-generated names like `Street1`. A migration will rename columns.

**b) Nested complex types use full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` now maps to column `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was `BillingAddress_City`).

**Fix both** by pinning column names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, a =>
    {
        a.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, a =>
    {
        a.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

// Nested example
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
    {
        p.ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress, a =>
        {
            a.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

All methods like `CommandReaderExecuting` now require an additional `string logCommandText` parameter:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new: redacted SQL for safe logging
    { /* logging — use logCommandText instead of command.CommandText */ }
}
```

Update **every** method on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
